# NICo public roadmap: v2.0, v2.1, v2.2, v2.3+, and 2027+

This page summarizes the current direction for NVIDIA Infra Controller (NICo). NICo provides site-local bare-metal lifecycle management for AI infrastructure, including hardware lifecycle operations, multitenant networking, and DPU-based isolation.

This roadmap is directional, not a commitment to ship every item listed. Scope, sequencing, and release targets can change as maintainers learn from users, contributors, partners, and production deployments.

Use the public milestones and tracking issues for the most current implementation status:

* [NICo milestones](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/milestones)

If a roadmap item does not yet have a public tracking issue, please open one before starting implementation work.

## v2.0: RMS, DPF, and API unification

Target window: July 2026

v2.0 focuses on making NICo's core surfaces more consistent and operable: REST API and `nicocli` parity, monorepo and single-versioning work, Helm and documentation alignment, Rack Management System (RMS) support, DPF-backed DPU management, and Zero-DPU support.

### Priority areas:

* REST API and `nicocli` parity for core admin operations, including power, BMC reset, DPU reprovisioning, health overrides, and site-wide BMC credential setup: [#1927](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/1927)
* DPF integration and making DPF the default DPU management path: [#672](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/672)
* Zero-DPU host support for environments where DPU installation is unavailable or unsuitable: [#870](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/870)
* Rack management through RMS, including switch, power shelf, compute tray, and NMX-C workflows: [#1408](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/1408), [#1409](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/1409), [#2420](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2420), [#2463](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2463)
* Component Manager integration with RMS for NVOS password rotation, NVOS updates, and NMX-C configuration: [#2041](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2041)
* Health management APIs for switches, power shelves, and racks: [#240](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/240)

### Operational hardening in scope:

* Predefined BMC IP allocation for expected machines: [#790](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/790)
* Default and site-wide BMC credential handling during ingestion: [#1294](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/1294)
* Clearer handling when config file changes do not take effect after initial deployment: [#933](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/933)
* DPU firmware management in NIC mode: [#2246](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2246)
* Redfish diagnostic payload forwarding for downstream log consumers: [#2817](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2817)

## v2.1: GB300 support and operational enhancements

Target window: August 2026

v2.1 focuses on GB300 readiness, deployment hardening, stability, usability, simulation at scale, and reducing operational complexity.

### Priority areas:

* GB300 NVL72 support: [#256](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/256)
* Vault dependency removal and migration toward simpler managed-secret and token-based authentication flows: [#195](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/195)
* Managed password lifecycle automation, including rotation and revocation: [#367](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/367)
* Follow-up REST API, OpenAPI, `nicocli`, and documentation parity after the v2.0 admin workflow audit: [#2852](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2852)
* Observability reference architecture for logs, metrics, traces, dashboards, and alerting: [#1989](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/1989)
* Per-object lifecycle progress observability for machines, instances, hosts, DPUs, state transitions, and manual intervention: [#2186](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2186)
* Health Check Library MVP for post-repair validation: [#2962](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2962)

### Operational and scale improvements:

* Task sequence customization for built-in rack and tray lifecycle operations: [#2072](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2072)
* Site-wide phased operation runs for large-scale firmware updates and other controlled operations: [#3131](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/3131)
* Firmware object model to unbundle firmware artifacts and versions from core/backend deployment: [#2114](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2114)
* BMC proxy and DPS-facing power provisioning flows: [#2092](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2092), [#3298](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/3298), [#991](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/991), [#2356](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2356)
* Local and scale simulation improvements through `nico-machine-a-tron`: [#3289](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/3289)

## v2.2: next-generation platform enablement

Target window: September 2026

v2.2 focuses on next-generation platform support and the control-plane capabilities needed for newer rack, DPU, networking, power, and trust workflows.

### Priority areas:

* Vera Rubin NVL72 support: [#258](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/258)
* BlueField-4 support: [#257](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/257)
* DPF changes for Astra, including service support, DPU deployment variants, hardware-triggered reprovisioning, multi-reboot flows, and Spectrum-X configuration handling: [#3205](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/3205)
* Spectrum-X partitioning and multitenancy: [#259](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/259), [#2238](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2238)
* DPS integration for NVSwitch and power provisioning workflows: [#2051](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2051), [#2092](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2092)
* Domain-level topology, power control, and firmware update APIs that can extend beyond racks to rows, scalable units, and larger domains: [#2080](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2080)
* Automation framework for state-, event-, and time-triggered task execution: [#2073](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2073)

### Trust, validation, and platform services:

* REST and `nicocli` support for measurables and trust approve rules: [#2801](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2801)
* DPU device identity using BlueField IRoT for node identity bootstrap without mTLS: [#2917](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2917)
* NICo attestation SRD and SADD: [#3099](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/3099)
* Rack validation and multinode test framework: [#416](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/416)
* Machine validation operator visibility and control: [#453](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/453)
* Health history for switches, power shelves, and racks: [#1384](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/1384)
* Tenant-visible instance health status: [#214](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/214)

### API and networking improvements:

* Routing Profile lifecycle management through REST API: [#2624](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2624)
* IP block ownership migration into NICo Core: [#2145](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2145)
* Redfish session-token usage for BMC-facing services: [#460](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/460), [#2853](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2853)

## v2.3+: IPv6 readiness and stateless API direction

Target window: rest of 2026 H2

v2.3+ focuses on IPv6 readiness, API simplification, and the next layer of operational automation.

### Priority areas:

* IPv6 support across managed hosts, BMC networks, DHCP, EVPN, overlay networks, IP allocations, monitoring, and Spectrum-X networks: [#84](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/84)
* IPv6 DPU/agent support: [#1264](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/1264)
* IPv6 bug scan and readiness bucket: [#2237](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2237)
* Critical IPv6 bug fixes, including `/64` allocation, BMC URL formatting, tenant IPv6 route leaking, IPv6 nameserver propagation, and IPv6 capacity reporting: [#2239](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2239), [#2240](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2240), [#2241](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2241), [#2242](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2242), [#2243](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2243)
* Dual-stack overlay, EVPN, DHCP, DNS, and customer documentation work: [#2414](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2414), [#2417](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2417), [#2385](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2385), [#2628](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2628)
* NICo REST MCP support for read-only API operations: [#2006](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2006)

### Needs tracking issue:

* Stateless REST API direction and scope.

## 2027+: ecosystem expansion and governance

Target window: 2027 and beyond

The longer-term roadmap expands NICo across partner hardware, modular networking, ecosystem integration, and community governance.

### Priority areas:

* Hardware enablement, including PowerEdge XE9780 support: [#3227](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/3227)
* LPX rack deployment evaluation and enablement: [#2818](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/2818)
* Modular SDN controller mode for external SDN controllers and partner networking stacks: [#982](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/982)
* Partner integration guidance, including storage vendor integration boundaries: [#3059](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/3059)
* Dashboards packaged in the repository and installable through Helm charts: [#1696](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/1696)
* Unified instrumentation standard for logs and metrics: [#3169](https://github.com/NVIDIA/infra-controller/issues/3169)

### Needs tracking issue:

* NVCert or equivalent certification flow for additional vendor-driven hardware support.
* Full IPv6 single-stack release criteria.
* OSS community governance model.

## Contribution Areas

These are the highest-impact areas for community and partner contributions:

* Documentation: upgrade paths, operator runbooks, and roadmap maintenance.
* Platform enablement: GB300, Vera Rubin, BlueField-4, Astra, LPX, and partner hardware validation.
* Rack operations: DPS, domain-level topology, power, firmware, and phased operation workflows.
* DPF and DPU lifecycle: DPF-managed DPU provisioning, standalone DPU provisioning, DPU identity, DPU services, and reprovisioning flows.
* Networking: IPv6, Spectrum-X, Routing Profiles, IP blocks, Modular SDN, overlay routing, DHCP, DNS, and EVPN.
* Observability and operations: dashboards, metrics, logs, traces, health history, state progress, alerting, and large-scale incident workflows.
* Security and trust: Vault removal, token auth, managed-secret lifecycle, attestation, trust approve rules, and Redfish session tokens.
* Simulation and testing: `nico-machine-a-tron`, host firmware simulation, DHCP simulation, IPMI/SOL simulation, and large-scale workflow testing.
